WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:03.754
She's smart. She's tough.
She'll fight for ya.

00:03.754 --> 00:05.380
I've been impressed with her
every time.

00:05.380 --> 00:07.007
How many times
have you been sued?

00:07.007 --> 00:08.550
Twice, just twice.

00:08.550 --> 00:10.886
But when you run a hospital,
it's good to know a good lawyer.

00:10.886 --> 00:12.387
Aaron!

00:12.387 --> 00:14.014
Janet, hi.

00:14.014 --> 00:15.724
Oh, my gosh.
Did it happen?

00:15.724 --> 00:17.267
Did you play Pebble Beach?

00:17.267 --> 00:18.977
I did, and it was the worst
mistake of my life.

00:18.977 --> 00:20.103
[ Laughs ]
Hello.

00:20.103 --> 00:21.605
I am
Dr. Shaun Murphy

00:21.605 --> 00:23.524
of San Jose
St. Bonaventure Hospital.

00:23.524 --> 00:25.234
Your client. Yes.

00:25.234 --> 00:27.277
Aaron has told me
a lot about you.

00:27.277 --> 00:28.445
Congratulations
on all you--

00:28.445 --> 00:29.529
Is this billable time?

00:29.529 --> 00:32.115
It is.

00:32.115 --> 00:34.493
But it will be paid for
by your insurance company.

00:34.493 --> 00:36.161
And I have good news.

00:37.955 --> 00:42.167
$300,000 that will be paid
by your malpractice insurance.

00:42.167 --> 00:44.086
All you have to do
is sign some documents

00:44.086 --> 00:47.214
and agree to
a six-month supervisory period.

00:47.214 --> 00:49.007
You can still
practice medicine.

00:49.007 --> 00:50.259
It just means
another doctor

00:50.259 --> 00:51.593
would have to sign off
on all your decisions.

00:51.593 --> 00:53.303
Excuse me.

00:53.303 --> 00:54.596
That is not good news.

00:58.600 --> 01:00.310
Can it be anyone?

01:00.310 --> 01:01.979
Anyone qualified.

01:01.979 --> 01:05.315
So Park, M-Morgan.

01:05.315 --> 01:06.692
It could be anyone you trust.
Could be me.

01:06.692 --> 01:10.112
I have worked very hard
to be an attending

01:10.112 --> 01:12.155
to prove that I don't need
anyone's approval

01:12.155 --> 01:14.324
to do what I think
should be done.

01:14.324 --> 01:16.493
Which is often different
from what Dr. Park, or Morgan,

01:16.493 --> 01:18.078
or you
think should be done.

01:19.663 --> 01:23.083
Also...
it is very humiliating.

01:26.128 --> 01:28.088
What if he says no?
We go to trial.

01:28.088 --> 01:30.173
And if he loses
at trial?

01:30.173 --> 01:32.843
The money will still be paid
by the insurance company.

01:32.843 --> 01:35.012
But the bigger issue
is that a report,

01:35.012 --> 01:36.305
and the court's decision,

01:36.305 --> 01:38.265
will be sent to
the California Medical Board,

01:38.265 --> 01:41.143
and they will make
a decision about whether...

01:41.143 --> 01:42.603
you have a future
as a doctor.

01:42.603 --> 01:47.941
♪

01:47.941 --> 01:49.192
I'll settle.

01:52.904 --> 01:54.990
I need to go to
the bathroom.

02:05.167 --> 02:07.294
Excuse me, excuse me,
excuse me.

02:07.294 --> 02:10.630
You're Dr. Shaun Murphy,

02:10.630 --> 02:11.715
Ms. Stewart's 10:00 a. m.?

02:11.715 --> 02:12.758
Yes, hello.

02:12.758 --> 02:15.385
My name is Joni DeGroot.

02:15.385 --> 02:19.097
Um... I'm curious about
cancer patients

02:19.097 --> 02:21.183
whose exposure
came from formaldehyde

02:21.183 --> 02:23.894
in pressed wood
office furniture.

02:23.894 --> 02:25.270
Have you had
a case like that?

02:25.270 --> 02:27.898
No. Nor have I read
about that.

02:27.898 --> 02:30.108
If you have a case where
that is alleged,

02:30.108 --> 02:31.526
I would not be
a good consultant.

02:31.526 --> 02:32.527
It's not for a case.

02:32.527 --> 02:34.488
It's...

02:34.488 --> 02:37.199
Thank you. Thank you,
thank you, Dr. Murphy.

02:37.199 --> 02:39.618
Tell Ms. Stewart
to review my update

02:39.618 --> 02:42.788
on Carter v. Willis
before finalizing your NDA.

02:42.788 --> 02:45.248
The Idaho District Court made
the stare decisis vulnerable.

02:45.248 --> 03:00.222
♪

03:00.222 --> 03:02.683
Are you working
on my case?

03:02.683 --> 03:04.768
You should not be
in here.

03:04.768 --> 03:06.144
This is my office.

03:06.144 --> 03:08.355
No one is supposed
to come into my office.

03:08.355 --> 03:10.023
Okay.

03:15.153 --> 03:18.407
I'm not officially
on your case.

03:18.407 --> 03:20.409
But I read the file.

03:20.409 --> 03:22.244
It was amazing how you created
arterial clamps

03:22.244 --> 03:23.662
out of pieces
of an aluminum can.

03:23.662 --> 03:26.164
Yes. Why is everything
covered in plastic?

03:26.164 --> 03:27.874
They're getting ready
to paint.

03:27.874 --> 03:29.167
Oh, I thought
it was because

03:29.167 --> 03:31.253
of your obsessive-compulsive
disorder.

03:34.381 --> 03:36.633
I used to have a closet
for an office.

03:36.633 --> 03:38.969
Did you choose this
instead of sharing an office?

03:38.969 --> 03:40.011
It's not a closet.
It's an office.

03:40.011 --> 03:41.263
It is very small.

03:41.263 --> 03:43.265
Even smaller
than my closet.

03:43.265 --> 03:45.809
This is all I need.
I don't meet with clients.

03:45.809 --> 03:47.561
And it's very private,
so I'm not disturbed

03:47.561 --> 03:48.562
while I'm doing
my research...

03:48.562 --> 03:49.521
Or your rituals.

03:51.440 --> 03:53.024
Nice to meet you,
Joni DeGroot.

03:53.024 --> 03:54.526
You're settling
your case?

03:56.528 --> 03:57.821
Yes.

03:57.821 --> 03:59.406
Ms. Stewart
and Dr. Glassman

03:59.406 --> 04:01.658
say it is
for the best.

04:01.658 --> 04:03.743
Your settlement includes
a supervisory period?

04:03.743 --> 04:06.037
Mm... yes.
Six months.

04:06.037 --> 04:07.873
Hmm.

04:07.873 --> 04:10.959
It doesn't seem right.
Does it?

04:10.959 --> 04:14.087
That-- That you
should be punished

04:14.087 --> 04:16.047
for saving
a man's life?

04:17.757 --> 04:19.718
You've overcome a lot.

04:19.718 --> 04:22.888
To have that kind of mark
on your record...

04:22.888 --> 04:25.307
seems very humiliating.

04:25.307 --> 04:29.603
♪

04:29.603 --> 04:32.314
I see you're still
in the big office. Ah.

04:32.314 --> 04:34.524
The partner uprising wasn't
as bad as you feared, huh?

04:34.524 --> 04:36.485
It's an ongoing battle.

04:36.485 --> 04:38.111
[ Knock on door ]

04:38.111 --> 04:39.821
Joni,
I'm with a client.

04:41.865 --> 04:43.116
No, she is.

04:45.243 --> 04:46.953
Joni is my lawyer now.

04:46.953 --> 04:49.498
She will be representing me
at trial.

04:49.498 --> 04:58.006
♪

04:58.006 --> 05:00.842
- Captions by VITAC--

05:00.842 --> 05:07.808
♪

05:11.686 --> 05:13.605
I have a new lawyer.

05:15.690 --> 05:17.317
I have a new client.

05:17.317 --> 05:19.319
<i>How did you get the partners
to change their minds?</i>

05:19.319 --> 05:21.738
The client insisted
that I represent him

05:21.738 --> 05:23.114
instead of Janet Stewart.

05:24.699 --> 05:25.951
<i>What?</i>

05:25.951 --> 05:28.328
♪ If I felt this way before ♪

05:28.328 --> 05:29.329
[ Door closes ]

05:29.329 --> 05:32.165
♪ Now I do not recall ♪

05:32.165 --> 05:33.792
You stole
your boss's client?

05:33.792 --> 05:35.877
♪ If we go ♪

05:35.877 --> 05:37.379
And what does Glassman
think about this?

05:37.379 --> 05:40.257
He said it was
my decision.

05:40.257 --> 05:44.302
Did he say that in a neutral way
or an angry way?

05:44.302 --> 05:47.889
♪ Then I am gonna fall down ♪

05:47.889 --> 05:50.350
Angry.

05:50.350 --> 05:53.061
He is worried about
Joni's lack of experience.

05:53.061 --> 05:55.522
But she's smart,
and because of her OCD,

05:55.522 --> 05:58.316
she is very thorough
and understands my situation.

05:58.316 --> 05:59.860
OCD.

05:59.860 --> 06:02.070
You mean she's really
neat and organized?

06:02.070 --> 06:03.363
No, that is not OCD.

06:03.363 --> 06:05.198
She has repetitive
intrusive thoughts

06:05.198 --> 06:06.533
that cause
excessive anxiety

06:06.533 --> 06:09.119
which she manages
with ritual behavior.

06:10.829 --> 06:13.456
And when you say
lack of experience?

06:13.456 --> 06:16.126
This will be
her first trial.

06:16.126 --> 06:18.086
♪ Really and truly, maybe ♪

06:18.086 --> 06:21.339
I get to go to court.
I get to be a real lawyer.

06:21.339 --> 06:23.925
Which is great,
very exciting,

06:23.925 --> 06:26.636
but it's also... court.

06:26.636 --> 06:30.724
All those people-- the judge,
the jury, the other lawyers,

06:30.724 --> 06:33.059
and everyone
looking at you...

06:33.059 --> 06:37.147
watching while you
do that.

06:37.147 --> 06:40.233
I'm practicing exposure
to contaminants and noises.

06:40.233 --> 06:43.695
I can adapt.
I can hide it.

06:43.695 --> 06:46.489
But that's the upside
of your current setup.

06:46.489 --> 06:47.908
You don't have
to hide it.

06:47.908 --> 06:48.742
Because they're hiding <i>me.</i>

06:48.742 --> 06:53.997
♪

06:53.997 --> 06:56.249
Mm.
[ Exhales deeply ]

06:56.249 --> 06:59.377
♪ Really and truly, maybe ♪

06:59.377 --> 07:01.880
♪ Really and truly,
it might be ♪

07:01.880 --> 07:03.715
Pockets.

07:03.715 --> 07:06.051
Your outfits for court
will need pockets.

07:06.051 --> 07:08.386
When you need to tap,
put your hand in there,

07:08.386 --> 07:09.971
no one will know.

07:09.971 --> 07:13.850
♪

07:13.850 --> 07:17.103
Just... don't be late.

07:18.104 --> 07:19.230
You're late.

07:23.318 --> 07:24.694
I thought you had this
worked out.

07:24.694 --> 07:26.363
I know, I know, I know. Sorry.

07:26.363 --> 07:29.157
The-- The bus stalled
right in the middle of Hastings.

07:29.157 --> 07:31.576
Do you want me to call the VTA
and check if that's true?

07:33.411 --> 07:34.954
No.

07:34.954 --> 07:36.039
Sorry.
It won't happen again.

07:43.630 --> 07:45.507
The night of the accident,
you were coming from where?

07:45.507 --> 07:47.759
I was giving Shaun
a lift home.

07:47.759 --> 07:50.095
We had grabbed dinner
together after work.

07:50.095 --> 07:52.263
Did either of you
have alcohol with dinner?

07:52.263 --> 07:55.725
I, uh... had a beer,

07:55.725 --> 07:57.727
and, um, Shaun didn't.

07:57.727 --> 08:01.439
Joni, your tapping
is distracting Dr. Park.

08:01.439 --> 08:03.066
I'm okay.

08:05.735 --> 08:07.696
[ Thinking ] <i>Tap three times
or bad things will happen.</i>

08:07.696 --> 08:10.490
Your shift that day,
how long was it?

08:10.490 --> 08:13.034
Did you or Dr. Murphy
have any difficult surgeries?

08:13.034 --> 08:14.327
Uh, nothing unusual.

08:14.327 --> 08:15.995
[ Distorted ]
I had an appendectomy,

08:15.995 --> 08:18.415
22-year-old patient,
no issues.

08:18.415 --> 08:20.208
<i>Tap three times
or bad things will happen.</i>

08:20.208 --> 08:21.543
Shaun performed
a bowel resection.

08:21.543 --> 08:25.422
<i>Tap three times
or bad things will happen.</i>

08:25.422 --> 08:27.298
<i>Tap three times or bad things
will happen.</i>

08:27.298 --> 08:28.758
Janet:
[ Distorted ] Joni...

08:28.758 --> 08:31.010
<i>Tap three times
or bad things will happen.</i>

08:31.010 --> 08:32.721
Joni.

08:32.721 --> 08:34.848
I'm sure you have
more questions for Dr. Park.

08:42.856 --> 08:45.316
You and Dr. Murphy left
the restaurant around what time?

08:45.316 --> 08:48.111
Uh, a little
after 10:30 p. m.

08:48.111 --> 08:49.696
We were on Hellyer,

08:49.696 --> 08:51.614
coming through the wooded
section of the park...

08:51.614 --> 08:54.034
and between the rain
and the turns,

08:54.034 --> 08:55.785
I was driving
pretty slowly.

08:55.785 --> 08:58.621
[ Thunder rumbles ]

08:58.621 --> 09:01.458
♪

09:01.458 --> 09:04.210
Good thing--
there was a car in the road.

09:04.210 --> 09:09.883
♪

09:09.883 --> 09:12.677
[ Woman groaning ]

09:14.846 --> 09:17.474
I'm a doctor.
My name is Alex Park.

09:17.474 --> 09:19.434
I need to examine--
Where is Bob?

09:19.434 --> 09:21.811
I need you to hold still.
Scalp laceration.

09:23.855 --> 09:25.648
Was there anyone else
in the car?

09:25.648 --> 09:27.859
Yes.
My brother, Bob.

09:27.859 --> 09:28.651
He was driving.

09:32.530 --> 09:34.407
Hello?

09:34.407 --> 09:44.125
♪

09:44.125 --> 09:45.251
He was thrown out.

09:45.251 --> 09:56.054
♪

09:56.054 --> 09:57.097
Bob?

09:57.097 --> 10:04.395
♪

10:04.395 --> 10:05.438
Bob!

10:05.438 --> 10:08.233
♪

10:08.233 --> 10:09.651
I found Bob!

10:09.651 --> 10:12.946
He is bleeding
from his radial artery.

10:12.946 --> 10:19.244
♪

10:19.244 --> 10:20.453
We need to move him!

10:20.453 --> 10:22.080
I can't leave her!

10:22.080 --> 10:39.514
♪

10:39.514 --> 10:40.932
Okay, Bob.

10:40.932 --> 10:58.867
♪

10:58.867 --> 11:00.410
Joni: That's wrong.

11:00.410 --> 11:01.578
What?

11:01.578 --> 11:04.414
You didn't bring him
that way.

11:04.414 --> 11:06.875
Oh.
Yes, I did.

11:06.875 --> 11:08.793
No, you didn't.

11:08.793 --> 11:10.170
Yes, he did.

11:10.170 --> 11:11.421
No, he didn't.
You couldn't have.

11:11.421 --> 11:12.714
There was a log there.

11:12.714 --> 11:31.566
♪

11:31.566 --> 11:34.027
Most people's brains
prioritize details,

11:34.027 --> 11:35.862
weed out what seems unimportant.

11:35.862 --> 11:38.656
My brain doesn't.

11:38.656 --> 11:41.159
Why does it matter what route
Shaun took out of the woods?

11:41.159 --> 11:42.535
The case is ab--
Shaun: It matters

11:42.535 --> 11:45.455
because
if that way was blocked,

11:45.455 --> 11:49.250
I must have
taken him this way.

11:49.250 --> 11:50.919
I would've had to angle
the spinal board,

11:50.919 --> 11:52.629
which could've caused
neurological injury,

11:52.629 --> 11:54.339
which could mean
my neuro exam was off,

11:54.339 --> 11:57.425
which could mean...

11:57.425 --> 12:00.011
I didn't need
to amputate his hand.

12:00.011 --> 12:06.351
♪

12:06.351 --> 12:08.645
This seems like a good time
for a break.

12:11.439 --> 12:13.900
[ Pen clicking ]

12:19.530 --> 12:24.827
♪

12:24.827 --> 12:26.204
Tell me about
your decision

12:26.204 --> 12:29.207
to amputate
the plaintiff's hand.

12:29.207 --> 12:34.504
His breathing became labored,
and his pulse was thready.

12:34.504 --> 12:37.340
He had no capillary refill.

12:37.340 --> 12:39.550
His hand was
irreversibly damaged

12:39.550 --> 12:41.094
from lack of blood flow.

12:41.094 --> 12:43.179
It was leaking toxins
that would stop his heart

12:43.179 --> 12:44.889
before he reached
the hospital.

12:44.889 --> 12:46.724
I need to amputate
his hand.

12:46.724 --> 12:48.393
The ambulance
is two minutes away.

12:48.393 --> 12:52.063
But ambulances do not
carry amputation kits.

12:52.063 --> 12:54.357
There is no time.

12:54.357 --> 13:07.996
♪

13:07.996 --> 13:10.707
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

13:10.707 --> 13:23.136
♪

13:23.136 --> 13:25.972
Once I removed
the hand...

13:25.972 --> 13:28.224
we traveled safely
to the hospital.

13:31.269 --> 13:34.188
That's... not quite
how I remember it.

13:34.188 --> 13:40.194
♪

13:40.194 --> 13:42.071
The ambulance
is two minutes away!

13:42.071 --> 13:44.115
I need to amputate
his hand.

13:44.115 --> 13:45.616
There's no time.

13:45.616 --> 13:48.953
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

13:48.953 --> 13:52.915
Shaun!
It could be a vasospasm!

13:52.915 --> 13:54.167
The ambulance is here!

13:54.167 --> 13:56.044
They'll have
a calcium channel blocker

13:56.044 --> 13:57.795
that might restore
the blood flow!

13:57.795 --> 14:02.675
♪

14:02.675 --> 14:05.386
Shaun, are you sure?!

14:05.386 --> 14:10.391
♪

14:16.689 --> 14:18.775
Interesting.

14:19.984 --> 14:21.778
This is a disaster.

14:21.778 --> 14:23.112
He has to settle.

14:23.112 --> 14:25.406
You have to talk him
into accepting the settlement.

14:25.406 --> 14:27.617
No, it doesn't change
the underlying merits...

14:27.617 --> 14:28.868
It changes the testimony.

14:28.868 --> 14:30.745
It changes <i>our</i> testimony.

14:30.745 --> 14:32.288
One of our witnesses
is going to testify

14:32.288 --> 14:34.373
that our client screwed up.

14:34.373 --> 14:35.958
His view of the accident

14:35.958 --> 14:38.461
is almost exactly
what their expert--

14:38.461 --> 14:40.129
What are you doing?

14:40.129 --> 14:41.798
I'll talk to Dr. Park
and counsel him--

14:41.798 --> 14:43.341
No.
I mean to my books.

14:43.341 --> 14:45.301
I straightened one.

14:45.301 --> 14:46.803
Or two.

14:46.803 --> 14:47.887
Listen to me.

14:49.097 --> 14:52.100
[ Distorted ] Taking this case
to trial, with <i>that</i> client

14:52.100 --> 14:55.812
and you as counsel,
is a terrible idea.
<i>Fix this
or bad things will happen.</i>

14:55.812 --> 14:59.816
You cannot win a case if
the jury doesn't like you...

14:59.816 --> 15:01.484
if you make them uncomfortable.

15:01.484 --> 15:04.320
<i>Fix this
or bad things will happen.</i>
Cases are stories.

15:04.320 --> 15:06.364
<i>Fix this or bad things
will happen.</i>
And we write it all.
Except the ending.

15:06.364 --> 15:08.658
<i>Fix this
or bad things will happen.</i>

15:08.658 --> 15:10.451
<i>Fix this or bad things
will happen.</i>

15:13.496 --> 15:14.497
[ Exhales deeply ]

15:14.497 --> 15:17.166
You can't control yourself
in my office.

15:17.166 --> 15:20.294
How are you gonna
control yourself in court?

15:20.294 --> 15:23.339
♪

15:23.339 --> 15:25.466
Texas v. Marquez.

15:25.466 --> 15:26.717
What?

15:26.717 --> 15:29.470
425 Federal Digest,
page 734.

15:29.470 --> 15:31.597
Um, you're gonna have
to give me a little more--

15:31.597 --> 15:35.184
Owen Marquez was caught
entering his high school

15:35.184 --> 15:36.644
carrying
a Swiss army knife.

15:36.644 --> 15:39.605
He was charged with being on
school property with a weapon.

15:39.605 --> 15:42.024
But they'd set up
the metal detectors

15:42.024 --> 15:45.361
<i>outside</i> the front door.

15:45.361 --> 15:47.280
The case was dismissed.

15:47.280 --> 15:49.031
Interesting.

15:49.031 --> 15:52.410
But different state,
different court, different law.

15:52.410 --> 15:53.661
Same principle.

15:53.661 --> 15:55.705
I don't think I can convince
a judge that that is--

15:55.705 --> 15:56.956
Let me try.

15:56.956 --> 16:00.251
[ Cellphone chimes ]

16:00.251 --> 16:01.502
[ Gasps ]

16:01.502 --> 16:02.670
Oh, I have to go.

16:02.670 --> 16:05.923
♪

16:09.927 --> 16:11.679
Stop. Stop. Stop.

16:11.679 --> 16:14.265
I'm about to test the lactate
levels in Bob's hand.

16:14.265 --> 16:16.934
This will prove definitively
if I was right to amputate.

16:16.934 --> 16:18.019
No. This will
tell you nothing.

16:18.019 --> 16:19.770
Medically, it will.

16:19.770 --> 16:21.689
Legally, morally,
this'll tell you nothing.

16:21.689 --> 16:23.524
This test will tell me
the truth.

16:23.524 --> 16:25.735
[ Scoffs ]

16:25.735 --> 16:28.654
Was... that a laugh?

16:28.654 --> 16:30.198
It was a scoff.

16:30.198 --> 16:32.658
Why would you scoff
at the truth?

16:32.658 --> 16:34.035
What truth?

16:34.035 --> 16:35.745
There's only one.

16:35.745 --> 16:38.831
There's a single correct answer
to any question.

16:38.831 --> 16:40.166
But there are a lot
of questions.

16:40.166 --> 16:41.792
You're asking, "What was
the right thing to do then,

16:41.792 --> 16:43.127
given what
you know now?"

16:43.127 --> 16:44.462
Which is
a stupid question.

16:44.462 --> 16:46.380
I don't like to use
the word "stupid."

16:46.380 --> 16:47.548
"Desperate" then.

16:47.548 --> 16:48.758
For an answer.

16:48.758 --> 16:50.134
But whatever
that test says,

16:50.134 --> 16:52.053
we have to share it
with the other side.

16:52.053 --> 16:53.054
If it goes the way
you want,

16:53.054 --> 16:54.388
we will definitely
win your case.

16:54.388 --> 16:55.431
If it goes
the other way,

16:55.431 --> 16:57.475
we will definitely
lose your case.

16:57.475 --> 17:00.353
But neither result will tell you
if you did the right thing,

17:00.353 --> 17:03.731
given what you knew
at the time.

17:03.731 --> 17:06.275
So the real
question here is--

17:06.275 --> 17:08.819
Do you believe in that test
more than you believe in me?

17:09.946 --> 17:24.293
♪

17:24.293 --> 17:26.921
Why?

17:26.921 --> 17:30.925
Why am I doing
what you just asked me to do?

17:30.925 --> 17:33.719
Why do you have
so much confidence in me?

17:35.763 --> 17:39.767
I'm a lawyer with OCD.

17:39.767 --> 17:42.562
I work out of a closet.

17:42.562 --> 17:45.106
I was late to the only meeting
you had with me.

17:45.106 --> 17:47.191
Why do you trust me
more than the test?

17:51.153 --> 17:55.491
Because the test
doesn't care.

17:55.491 --> 18:00.204
♪

18:00.204 --> 18:01.414
That's a good answer.

18:01.414 --> 18:03.082
Hm.

18:06.168 --> 18:08.754
We're gonna have a motion to
dismiss tomorrow at 10:00 a. m.

18:08.754 --> 18:10.214
Don't be late.

18:10.214 --> 18:14.677
♪

18:21.434 --> 18:23.519
Young Joni: [ Whispering ]

18:23.519 --> 18:28.482
One, two, three.

18:28.482 --> 18:30.109
One, two...

18:30.109 --> 18:32.278
We'll be okay.

18:32.278 --> 18:34.697
Only if
I do this right.

18:34.697 --> 18:36.824
Now I have
to start over.

18:36.824 --> 18:40.494
[ Inhales deeply ]

18:40.494 --> 18:44.832
One, two, three.

18:44.832 --> 18:46.459
Mom will be okay.

18:48.461 --> 18:52.757
One, two, three.

18:52.757 --> 18:54.592
Joni DeGroot for the defense,
Your Honor.

18:54.592 --> 18:57.303
Yes, I can see your name
right here on top of your brief.

18:57.303 --> 18:59.096
Excellent. May I say
what a privilege it is--

18:59.096 --> 19:01.641
No.
No, you may not.

19:01.641 --> 19:03.976
You are just here
to argue this motion,

19:03.976 --> 19:08.981
which...
is a novel argument.

19:08.981 --> 19:10.691
Thank you, Your Honor.

19:10.691 --> 19:12.526
It wasn't completely
a compliment.

19:19.659 --> 19:21.452
Dr. Murphy cannot
be held liable

19:21.452 --> 19:23.579
for professional misconduct
because Dr. Murphy

19:23.579 --> 19:26.457
was not acting
in a professional capacity.

19:26.457 --> 19:27.458
He was a Good Samaritan.

19:27.458 --> 19:28.959
And you're taking
the position

19:28.959 --> 19:31.587
that The Good Samaritan
exception stayed in effect

19:31.587 --> 19:33.673
even after
the ambulance arrived?

19:33.673 --> 19:36.509
Yes, because he didn't do
the amputation <i>in</i> the ambulance.

19:36.509 --> 19:37.968
He was <i>outside</i>
the ambulance.

19:37.968 --> 19:40.012
He <i>chose</i> not to do the
amputation in the ambulance.

19:40.012 --> 19:41.806
To save your client's life.
He had no time.

19:41.806 --> 19:42.932
The ambulance
was right there.

19:42.932 --> 19:44.600
Right there?
What does that mean?

19:44.600 --> 19:47.478
Would it have been "right there"
if he was 10 feet away?

19:47.478 --> 19:49.772
100 feet?
Or a half a mile?

19:49.772 --> 19:51.357
All interesting questions
for another case.

19:51.357 --> 19:53.067
He was five feet away.

19:53.067 --> 19:54.694
Outside is outside.

19:54.694 --> 19:57.238
The statute specifies protection
if the care happens

19:57.238 --> 19:58.989
<i>at</i> the scene
of an emergency.

19:58.989 --> 20:01.200
Counsel is using a technical
distinction that--

20:01.200 --> 20:03.202
Counsel is using the law.

20:03.202 --> 20:05.621
Statutory interpretation rules
require, Your Honor,

20:05.621 --> 20:07.665
to "give effect, if possible,
to every clause

20:07.665 --> 20:09.625
and word of a statute,
avoiding, if it may be,

20:09.625 --> 20:12.461
any construction which implies
that the legislature..."
[ Chair squeaks ]

20:12.461 --> 20:18.759
<i>Two more squeaks.</i>

20:26.559 --> 20:28.602
You just stopped?

20:28.602 --> 20:30.646
I lost my train
of thought.

20:30.646 --> 20:32.022
You said you didn't think
you could win this motion--

20:32.022 --> 20:33.983
I would've finished it.

20:36.736 --> 20:38.362
I...

20:40.322 --> 20:42.366
I heard a squeak.

20:42.366 --> 20:44.660
[ Sighs ]

20:44.660 --> 20:48.164
I needed two more squeaks
to complete the set.

20:51.751 --> 20:55.629
They pulled
the settlement offer.

20:55.629 --> 20:57.965
And... the partners met.

20:57.965 --> 20:59.467
[ Clears throat ]
You're off the case.

21:02.344 --> 21:04.597
They told you--
Mm. The vote was unanimous.

21:09.769 --> 21:11.729
You are
a good researcher.

21:11.729 --> 21:15.024
You are a database
that thinks.

21:15.024 --> 21:18.402
But you need to accept
that you are not,

21:18.402 --> 21:21.113
and you are never going to be,
a good lawyer.

21:23.783 --> 21:25.242
Shaun: No, no, no.

21:25.242 --> 21:27.244
Joni is my lawyer.

21:27.244 --> 21:29.330
It is my case,
my choice.

21:29.330 --> 21:32.249
Janet: And your <i>career</i>
that's riding on this.

21:34.210 --> 21:36.712
Joni's deficits
are more significant

21:36.712 --> 21:38.297
than you think they are.

21:38.297 --> 21:40.257
Everybody said that about me.
Everybody was wr--

21:40.257 --> 21:42.927
Do you know why her office
is a closet?

21:42.927 --> 21:45.054
Joni has had issues
since she started here.

21:45.054 --> 21:47.640
She was late a lot.

21:47.640 --> 21:51.060
Her first assignment,
her first motion, she missed it.

21:51.060 --> 21:53.854
She must have had
a good reason.

21:53.854 --> 21:55.397
She saw
someone drowning.

21:55.397 --> 21:56.732
Oh.

21:56.732 --> 21:58.275
She was on her way
to court,

21:58.275 --> 22:00.152
driving by the bay,
and she saw something.

22:00.152 --> 22:02.154
She stopped,
called the police.

22:02.154 --> 22:04.448
They shut down the road,
searched the water.

22:04.448 --> 22:06.826
Joni knew she saw...

22:06.826 --> 22:10.079
a log, a wave--
nothing.

22:10.079 --> 22:12.790
But her mind wouldn't let her
accept that it was nothing.

22:14.750 --> 22:17.920
We found out this had happened
twice before.

22:17.920 --> 22:20.089
Why didn't you fire her?

22:20.089 --> 22:22.258
Because she threatened
to sue us,

22:22.258 --> 22:24.552
arguing that firing her
would be a violation

22:24.552 --> 22:27.221
of the American's
With Disabilities Act.

22:27.221 --> 22:28.472
Was it?
I'm not sure.

22:28.472 --> 22:29.849
I don't think so.

22:29.849 --> 22:33.227
But this brief
that she wrote...

22:33.227 --> 22:35.104
most impressive thing
I've ever read.

22:36.772 --> 22:38.691
So she doesn't need
an office,

22:38.691 --> 22:40.109
because she doesn't need
to meet with clients

22:40.109 --> 22:43.279
because she does research.

22:43.279 --> 22:44.238
Just research.

22:46.407 --> 22:48.534
She cannot be
your trial attorney.

22:48.534 --> 22:53.914
♪

22:53.914 --> 22:55.916
I hate her.
I don't.

22:55.916 --> 22:58.335
She stuffed you in a closet.
Set you up to fail.

22:58.335 --> 22:59.378
You know
she's done more.

22:59.378 --> 23:00.796
She hired me.
She saved--

23:00.796 --> 23:02.381
She sent you to court
on your own.

23:02.381 --> 23:03.757
What was she expecting?

23:03.757 --> 23:05.551
She expected me to do the job.
So did I.

23:07.761 --> 23:08.929
She could've
been there...

23:08.929 --> 23:13.183
It was my idea,
my argument, my case...

23:13.183 --> 23:14.810
my failure.

23:17.521 --> 23:18.939
[ Knock on door ]

23:23.986 --> 23:25.613
[ Door opens ]

23:26.989 --> 23:28.532
[ Door closes ]

23:28.532 --> 23:35.205
♪

23:35.205 --> 23:37.750
Why do you want
to be a lawyer?

23:37.750 --> 23:43.047
♪

23:47.718 --> 23:51.555
Why did you
threaten to sue?

23:51.555 --> 23:53.807
Why do you want
to be there?

23:53.807 --> 23:55.851
They're a very good
firm--

23:55.851 --> 23:58.812
i-interesting files,
important cases,

23:58.812 --> 24:00.731
and it's not like
I have huge options--

24:00.731 --> 24:03.275
No. I meant...

24:03.275 --> 24:05.527
why do you want
to be a lawyer?

24:08.739 --> 24:10.491
A lawyer
saved our family.

24:14.411 --> 24:18.123
Our father died
in a car accident when I was 8.

24:18.123 --> 24:20.501
That's when
my OCD started.

24:20.501 --> 24:22.252
I was very worried
that my mother would die, too.

24:22.252 --> 24:25.506
So you developed rituals
meant to prevent it?

24:25.506 --> 24:26.799
Mm.

24:28.092 --> 24:29.927
And she didn't die.

24:29.927 --> 24:31.971
But she did drink.

24:34.932 --> 24:37.101
Bad things happened.

24:37.101 --> 24:40.604
A lot of people
made a lot of mistakes--

24:40.604 --> 24:46.068
our mother, some overworked
social workers,

24:46.068 --> 24:49.863
some foster parents,
a judge.

24:52.408 --> 24:58.163
But one person
made it all right again--

24:58.163 --> 24:59.373
a lawyer.

24:59.373 --> 25:06.422
♪

25:06.422 --> 25:09.591
Joni...

25:09.591 --> 25:11.260
I still want you
as my lawyer.

25:11.260 --> 25:14.471
Dr. Murphy,
I made a huge mistake.

25:16.181 --> 25:18.559
Because...

25:18.559 --> 25:20.811
I have a problem.

25:20.811 --> 25:22.813
We all have problems.

25:26.567 --> 25:27.484
I'll talk to Janet.

25:27.484 --> 25:33.198
♪

25:35.242 --> 25:36.994
Dr. Murphy wants you
as first chair.

25:36.994 --> 25:38.370
So you're first chair.

25:38.370 --> 25:39.872
I'm first chair?
You are not first chair.

25:39.872 --> 25:41.206
I'm not first chair.

25:41.206 --> 25:42.624
You are a figurehead.

25:42.624 --> 25:44.752
You will sit in your first chair
and you will not say a word.

25:44.752 --> 25:46.879
You will not stand up.
You will not object.

25:46.879 --> 25:48.964
If you have to tap,
you will tap quietly...

25:48.964 --> 25:51.008
on your leg.

25:51.008 --> 25:52.801
Now wish me luck.

25:52.801 --> 25:54.011
Good luck.

25:55.929 --> 25:57.431
Ross: In your expert opinion,
when Dr. Murphy

25:57.431 --> 25:58.932
concluded that
my client's hand

25:58.932 --> 26:01.769
was irreversibly damaged
and needed to be amputated--

26:01.769 --> 26:03.270
He was wrong.

26:03.270 --> 26:04.938
The lack of blood flow
was caused

26:04.938 --> 26:07.775
by a temporary condition
known as vasospasm,

26:07.775 --> 26:11.195
which can occur after a trauma
such as a car accident.

26:11.195 --> 26:14.740
Vessels temporarily clamp down,
cutting off the flow of blood.

26:14.740 --> 26:17.743
In this case, Mr. Patton's
ulnar artery spasmed.

26:17.743 --> 26:19.161
And this condition
is treatable?

26:19.161 --> 26:22.664
Yes-- with an injection
of calcium channel blocker,

26:22.664 --> 26:24.500
which was available
in the ambulance that night.

26:24.500 --> 26:26.168
Hm.

26:26.168 --> 26:27.711
Thank you.

26:27.711 --> 26:29.004
Your witness.

26:30.547 --> 26:31.799
[ Quietly ]
Any last minute ideas?

26:31.799 --> 26:33.842
Anything we can challenge him
on medically?

26:33.842 --> 26:36.261
It wasn't vasospasm.

26:36.261 --> 26:38.180
Anything we could
prove?

26:38.180 --> 26:39.181
No.

26:42.726 --> 26:45.687
Janet: Dr. Rutenberg,
are you being paid

26:45.687 --> 26:48.565
by the Plaintiff's attorney
for your testimony today?
I am.

26:48.565 --> 26:49.691
[ Distorted ] Then you can
hardly consider yourself

26:49.691 --> 26:51.193
unbiased, can you?

26:51.193 --> 26:52.861
It's routine for experts
to be paid.

26:52.861 --> 26:54.196
You're being paid.

26:54.196 --> 26:56.073
And I admit,
I am biased--

26:56.073 --> 26:58.867
Excuse me, excuse me,
excuse me.

26:58.867 --> 27:02.246
Traumatic vasospasm doesn't
occur in isolated vessels,

27:02.246 --> 27:04.748
but rather the entire
affected limb, right?

27:04.748 --> 27:06.041
Yes, of course.

27:06.041 --> 27:08.252
Can you
visually identify

27:08.252 --> 27:10.921
a damaged or occluded vessel
versus one in vasospasm?

27:10.921 --> 27:12.548
Yes.

27:12.548 --> 27:13.674
So...

27:13.674 --> 27:20.180
♪

27:20.180 --> 27:21.431
this one?

27:21.431 --> 27:23.642
Occluded.

27:23.642 --> 27:29.481
Vasospasm.

27:29.481 --> 27:30.816
Occluded.

27:30.816 --> 27:33.026
Not vasospasm?

27:33.026 --> 27:34.945
No.
Objection, Your Honor.

27:34.945 --> 27:36.321
Is this testimony
or the MCAT?

27:36.321 --> 27:38.115
Goes to the witness'
expertise.

27:38.115 --> 27:39.491
Oh, he's definitely
an expert.

27:39.491 --> 27:44.329
That last photo,
which did not show vasospasm,

27:44.329 --> 27:47.791
that was a pathology image
of Mr. Patton's radial artery.

27:47.791 --> 27:49.585
And if his radial artery
didn't vasospasm,

27:49.585 --> 27:51.169
then according to
your expert testimony,

27:51.169 --> 27:52.212
his ulnar artery
didn't either.

27:52.212 --> 27:53.839
Is that correct?

27:53.839 --> 27:57.134
[ Sighs ] It's possible.

27:57.134 --> 27:58.886
But we'd only know for sure

27:58.886 --> 28:01.430
if Dr. Murphy had given
the calcium channel blocker.

28:01.430 --> 28:12.983
♪

28:12.983 --> 28:15.652
I'm sorry.
You're not great
at taking direction, are you?

28:15.652 --> 28:17.154
No, I shouldn't--
And you only still
have a job

28:17.154 --> 28:18.196
because you threatened
to sue us.

28:18.196 --> 28:20.657
I'm sorry!

28:20.657 --> 28:23.243
I'm not wanted
in a lot of places.

28:23.243 --> 28:26.204
I make people feel uncomfortable.

28:26.204 --> 28:29.291
If I let that stop me,
I wouldn't be anywhere.

28:29.291 --> 28:32.044
At my first job,
I was the only female associate.

28:35.422 --> 28:38.216
Tomorrow...

28:38.216 --> 28:40.177
you're first chair.

28:40.177 --> 28:42.429
Actual first chair.

28:42.429 --> 28:43.555
Good luck.

28:43.555 --> 28:50.103
♪

28:54.149 --> 28:56.735
Nice work.
This is good stuff.

28:56.735 --> 29:00.113
Thank you.
The carpal tunnel research
is really interesting.

29:00.113 --> 29:02.240
A pre-existing condition
mitigates our client's respon--

29:02.240 --> 29:03.659
I'm not gonna use that.

29:05.035 --> 29:06.662
It could help
reduce damages.

29:06.662 --> 29:09.456
If damages are even $1, it means
Dr. Murphy was negligent,

29:09.456 --> 29:11.333
which means his medical license
would be at risk.

29:11.333 --> 29:13.543
We need total victory.

29:13.543 --> 29:15.545
Okay. So what's
your theory on this?

29:15.545 --> 29:18.423
How are you going to approach
this witness?

29:18.423 --> 29:19.967
I'm going to establish
that he's a dick.

29:24.680 --> 29:26.056
I can't do my job.

29:27.933 --> 29:29.726
I can't even hold my niece.

29:35.774 --> 29:36.817
Ross: Thank you.

29:38.193 --> 29:41.154
No more questions,
Your Honor.

29:50.998 --> 29:53.208
Dr. Murphy
saved your life.

29:53.208 --> 29:54.668
Is that a question?

29:54.668 --> 29:56.378
Not really.
Seems pretty obvious.

29:56.378 --> 29:57.379
I meant--
I know what you meant.

29:57.379 --> 29:58.880
I'll rephrase.

29:58.880 --> 30:02.551
What kind of person sues
a person who saved their life?

30:02.551 --> 30:04.928
Do you sue people who buy you
Christmas presents

30:04.928 --> 30:06.388
you don't want,
or only the weird ones

30:06.388 --> 30:07.806
you figure the jury
won't like?

30:07.806 --> 30:09.933
Objection-- compound
and argumentative.

30:09.933 --> 30:11.685
Sustained.

30:11.685 --> 30:13.228
I'm the victim here.

30:13.228 --> 30:15.522
You were driving, right?

30:15.522 --> 30:17.315
Yes.
Over the speed limit?

30:17.315 --> 30:19.401
I'm not sure.

30:19.401 --> 30:22.779
According to police analysis
of your skid marks...

30:22.779 --> 30:25.991
Yes. A little.
...you were going at least
70 in 40 zone.

30:25.991 --> 30:28.201
You were ejected
out the car window?
Yes.

30:28.201 --> 30:29.911
So you weren't wearing
a seat belt?

30:29.911 --> 30:31.204
I'm not sure.

30:31.204 --> 30:32.330
It was fastened
behind you.

30:32.330 --> 30:34.249
[ Sighs ] Yes.

30:34.249 --> 30:36.710
So all things considered,

30:36.710 --> 30:40.088
maybe a better adjective
than "victim" would be "lucky".

30:40.088 --> 30:41.256
Withdrawn.

30:41.256 --> 30:43.842
Do you feel any guilt
over any of this?

30:43.842 --> 30:46.261
You're asking me
if I feel guilty

30:46.261 --> 30:48.346
about wanting to be compensated
for losing--
No.

30:48.346 --> 30:50.390
I am asking you
if you feel guilty

30:50.390 --> 30:52.642
about driving recklessly,
flipping your car,

30:52.642 --> 30:54.895
and almost
killing your sister...

30:54.895 --> 30:57.147
the mother
of your niece?

30:57.147 --> 30:59.149
Yeah, a little.

30:59.149 --> 31:01.693
Is she suing you f--

31:01.693 --> 31:02.986
[ Chair squeaks ]

31:02.986 --> 31:09.951
<i>Two more squeaks.</i>

31:09.951 --> 31:18.627
♪

31:18.627 --> 31:20.754
Judge Kileen: Counsel,
do we have a problem?

31:20.754 --> 31:22.422
Again?

31:22.422 --> 31:29.387
♪

31:29.387 --> 31:30.972
Uh, one moment.

31:34.476 --> 31:36.103
Don't win cheap.
You're better than this...

31:36.103 --> 31:38.021
I am fighting
for my client.

31:38.021 --> 31:40.232
If she can't handle
a little adversity,

31:40.232 --> 31:41.149
then she shouldn't
be here.

31:46.238 --> 31:48.907
Don't let that dick
prove people like me right.

31:56.540 --> 31:58.166
[ Chair squeaks ]
Hey, hey, hey.

31:58.166 --> 32:00.043
Ms. Stewart,
I will hold you in contempt.

32:04.631 --> 32:06.341
[ Chair squeaks ]

32:06.341 --> 32:09.302
If Dr. Murphy had been
a not nice person

32:09.302 --> 32:11.763
and just driven on,
you'd be dead.

32:11.763 --> 32:13.265
And his career wouldn't
hang in the balance.

32:13.265 --> 32:14.266
Ross: Uh, objection.

32:14.266 --> 32:16.184
Calls for speculation.
Not a lot.

32:16.184 --> 32:17.310
The objection
is sustained.

32:17.310 --> 32:18.603
Ms. Stewart,

32:18.603 --> 32:20.438
I am finding you
in contempt.

32:20.438 --> 32:23.150
That stunt
just cost you $5,000.

32:23.150 --> 32:25.527
You're lucky
it's not assault.

32:25.527 --> 32:28.947
Now, Ms. DeGroot...

32:28.947 --> 32:30.198
you may continue.

32:32.534 --> 32:35.370
Thank you, Your Honor.
Thank you, Your Honor.

32:35.370 --> 32:37.122
Mr. Patton, the night
of the accident...

32:41.042 --> 32:43.628
Hey.
I'm so sorry.

32:43.628 --> 32:45.630
I know that it
happened again...
Shut up.

32:45.630 --> 32:46.882
You're doing fantastic.

32:46.882 --> 32:48.675
But you still have
Murphy's testimony.

32:48.675 --> 32:50.260
We need the jury
to like him.

32:50.260 --> 32:52.679
They need to think
he did nothing wrong.

32:52.679 --> 32:56.016
Have you given thought to how
you're gonna do that?

32:56.016 --> 32:58.059
Yes. I have.

32:59.561 --> 33:01.897
Did you do anything wrong
at the scene of the accident?

33:01.897 --> 33:03.440
Objection. Leading.

33:03.440 --> 33:04.232
Yes.

33:06.860 --> 33:08.195
Withdrawn.

33:12.699 --> 33:15.452
I did
four things wrong.

33:15.452 --> 33:17.913
I applied the tourniquet
at the brachial artery

33:17.913 --> 33:19.539
instead of mid-forearm.

33:19.539 --> 33:22.334
I laid out the clamps <i>after</i>
the makeshift vascular clips.

33:22.334 --> 33:24.628
I only did two wipe downs
of the surgical field,

33:24.628 --> 33:26.963
and I angled the spinal board
as I moved Mr. Patton

33:26.963 --> 33:30.133
out of the woods
because a log was in the way.

33:30.133 --> 33:32.344
Were any of those mistakes
relevant?

33:32.344 --> 33:35.680
They were to me.

33:35.680 --> 33:39.351
But I don't believe they
affected the patient's outcome.

33:39.351 --> 33:41.770
Given where you sit today,
right now,

33:41.770 --> 33:43.939
do you think one of the things
that you and Dr. Park

33:43.939 --> 33:46.107
did wrong... was stopping?

33:47.150 --> 33:49.444
No. Then Mr. Patton
would be dead.

33:49.444 --> 33:52.989
And the amputation,
was that the right thing to do?

33:57.118 --> 33:58.912
I don't know.

33:58.912 --> 34:04.042
But I know that if I had
to do it all over again...

34:04.042 --> 34:06.419
I would stop,

34:06.419 --> 34:09.297
I would help,

34:09.297 --> 34:11.174
and I would amputate.

34:13.468 --> 34:15.971
Dr. Murphy,
you're different.

34:18.848 --> 34:20.934
Tell me about yourself.

34:20.934 --> 34:23.395
Objection.
Vague and irrelevant.

34:23.395 --> 34:26.439
Your challenges,
the obstacles you've overcome...

34:26.439 --> 34:28.566
Marginally less vague,
still completely irrelevant.

34:28.566 --> 34:30.610
And yet, I will allow.

34:30.610 --> 34:37.409
♪

34:37.409 --> 34:42.497
I have autism
spectrum disorder.

34:42.497 --> 34:46.042
I have always had
autism spectrum disorder.

34:47.502 --> 34:52.799
I have also always wanted
to be a doctor.

34:52.799 --> 34:55.885
Many people thought that
couldn't happen, but I saved...

35:01.016 --> 35:04.853
[ Muttering ]

35:07.647 --> 35:08.857
Hi.

35:11.151 --> 35:13.445
I think I'm better
at asking questions
than giving speeches.

35:13.445 --> 35:15.530
Closings are tricky.

35:15.530 --> 35:18.241
It helps to actually
say the words,

35:18.241 --> 35:19.784
not just mutter them.
[ Chuckles ]

35:19.784 --> 35:20.994
Can I say them now?

35:23.997 --> 35:26.499
You want my feedback?

35:26.499 --> 35:28.668
If I don't like it,
I'm going to tell you...

35:28.668 --> 35:29.919
bluntly.

35:29.919 --> 35:31.171
You know that, right?

35:31.171 --> 35:33.632
'Cause you've been so tactful
with me up till now?

35:33.632 --> 35:35.091
[ Chuckles ]

35:42.724 --> 35:45.769
[ Exhales deeply ]

35:45.769 --> 35:50.065
My mentor told me that
criminal law is about justice,

35:50.065 --> 35:55.820
whereas civil law is about
one thing and one thing only--

35:55.820 --> 35:57.947
money.

35:57.947 --> 36:02.077
You can't undo
what's been done.

36:02.077 --> 36:06.414
The best you can do
is compensate, financially.

36:06.414 --> 36:08.166
But that's wrong.

36:08.166 --> 36:11.002
Everything we do in this room
is about justice.

36:12.962 --> 36:14.589
We can't change
what's happened,

36:14.589 --> 36:20.261
but maybe, just maybe,
we can change what will happen.

36:20.261 --> 36:23.056
We can encourage
people to care,

36:23.056 --> 36:24.099
to care about strangers,
to care--

36:24.099 --> 36:25.517
That's not your closing.

36:25.517 --> 36:26.601
It's a good closing.

36:26.601 --> 36:28.061
It's a very good closing.

36:28.061 --> 36:30.563
It was your closing.
A long time ago.

36:30.563 --> 36:33.274
My mentor
said that to me.

36:33.274 --> 36:34.901
I developed it into
an effective clos--

36:34.901 --> 36:36.152
Did you believe it?

36:38.238 --> 36:41.199
About justice?
That we can change the future?

36:41.199 --> 36:42.951
I did.

36:44.703 --> 36:46.037
But not anymore?

36:49.708 --> 36:50.834
[ Chuckles ]

36:52.627 --> 36:54.754
Maybe if <i>my</i> mentor
gave me advice,

36:54.754 --> 36:57.465
I could turn it into
something effective.

36:57.465 --> 37:00.009
You consider me a mentor?

37:02.387 --> 37:04.389
You did inspire me.

37:07.142 --> 37:11.521
I will [chuckles]
give you one piece of advice.

37:15.442 --> 37:18.319
You're not me.

37:18.319 --> 37:20.780
Not once in this trial
have you done

37:20.780 --> 37:23.408
what I would've done.

37:23.408 --> 37:26.619
Or what I wanted you
to do.

37:26.619 --> 37:27.996
So far, it's worked.

37:31.583 --> 37:33.585
I see no reason
to change now.

37:33.585 --> 37:47.932
♪

37:47.932 --> 37:49.309
My mentor told me...

37:51.561 --> 37:53.772
My mentor told me...

37:54.731 --> 37:58.151
My mentor told me...

37:58.151 --> 38:01.696
that people
don't like me.

38:01.696 --> 38:04.282
That I make them uncomfortable.

38:04.282 --> 38:05.325
She's right.

38:07.577 --> 38:09.287
And people don't like
my client either.

38:12.373 --> 38:13.958
We're different.

38:15.376 --> 38:17.504
But we're all different.

38:17.504 --> 38:21.132
You-- You've worn purple
every day of this trial.

38:21.132 --> 38:23.343
I assume
because you love it.

38:23.343 --> 38:26.179
And 'cause you want it
to be your "thing."

38:26.179 --> 38:28.723
You've got
those mutton chops.

38:28.723 --> 38:30.600
They're great.
They're fun.

38:30.600 --> 38:33.603
They make you... you.

38:33.603 --> 38:35.522
But when we start to get judged
based on our differences,

38:35.522 --> 38:36.815
it's not fun anymore.

38:38.733 --> 38:40.902
And fair enough,
this is a courtroom.

38:40.902 --> 38:44.864
You are literally here
to judge my client.

38:44.864 --> 38:49.077
But please don't judge him
based on the way that he talks,

38:49.077 --> 38:52.038
or on how he doesn't
look at you,

38:52.038 --> 38:54.374
or on
his awkward mannerisms.

38:54.374 --> 38:56.668
Judge him...

38:56.668 --> 38:59.462
on who he is.

38:59.462 --> 39:01.381
At every moment of his life,

39:01.381 --> 39:03.216
he has tried to make
a difference,

39:03.216 --> 39:06.219
tried to make things
a little better.

39:06.219 --> 39:07.762
Please don't punish him
for that.

39:11.224 --> 39:12.892
Please...

39:12.892 --> 39:15.061
do what the plaintiff
should've done.

39:17.730 --> 39:19.023
Say thank you.

39:19.023 --> 39:39.294
♪ I think it's time
we found a way back home ♪

39:40.670 --> 39:44.465
♪ You lose so many things
you love as you grow ♪

39:47.385 --> 39:50.179
♪ I missed the days
when I was just a kid ♪

39:52.390 --> 39:56.185
♪ My fear became my shadow,
I swear it did ♪

40:00.231 --> 40:04.068
♪ Wherever is your heart
I call home ♪

40:05.528 --> 40:10.325
♪ Wherever is your heart
I call home ♪

40:10.325 --> 40:14.370
♪ Though your feet may take you
far from me, I know ♪

40:15.622 --> 40:20.293
♪ Wherever is your heart
I call home ♪

40:20.293 --> 40:28.217
♪ You made me feel like
I was always falling ♪

40:28.217 --> 40:31.971
♪ Always falling down
without a place to land ♪

40:33.765 --> 40:38.061
♪ Somewhere in the distance
I heard you calling ♪

40:38.061 --> 40:43.024
♪ Oh, it hurts so bad
to let go of your hand ♪

40:43.024 --> 40:48.237
♪ Though your feet may take you
far from me, I know ♪

40:48.237 --> 40:52.909
♪ Wherever is your heart
I call home ♪

40:52.909 --> 40:54.744
You are a good lawyer.

40:57.622 --> 40:59.248
Thank you.

41:01.167 --> 41:02.710
[ Door opens ]

41:02.710 --> 41:04.671
The jury's back.

41:04.671 --> 41:06.506
♪ I'm calling home ♪

41:06.506 --> 41:11.719
♪ Oh, God, forgive my mind ♪

41:11.719 --> 41:17.684
♪ When I come home ♪

41:17.684 --> 41:19.060
I won, Mom.

41:19.060 --> 41:20.937
She was brilliant.

41:20.937 --> 41:22.271
I think you need
to seriously consider

41:22.271 --> 41:23.690
picking a new
favorite child.

41:23.690 --> 41:25.400
We gotta go, Mom.

41:25.400 --> 41:26.609
People are buying Joni
lots of drinks.

41:26.609 --> 41:28.444
We love you.

41:28.444 --> 41:31.864
♪ Though your feet may take you
far from me, I know ♪

41:31.864 --> 41:33.825
I never doubted you.

41:33.825 --> 41:36.077
Yeah, you did.

41:36.077 --> 41:37.704
Because you love me.

41:39.622 --> 41:40.623
Shaun!

41:40.623 --> 41:44.252
Oh, Joni.
Tequila, stat!

41:44.252 --> 41:45.253
We did good, huh?

41:45.253 --> 41:47.380
We did very well.

41:47.380 --> 41:48.631
We need to celebrate.

41:48.631 --> 41:50.008
We are celebrating.

41:52.468 --> 41:54.846
This is definitely not what you
want to be doing right now.

41:57.432 --> 42:04.355
♪ Wherever is your heart
I call home ♪

42:04.355 --> 42:06.149
Don't you want
to see this?

42:06.149 --> 42:07.859
Nope.
Not my thing.

42:07.859 --> 42:12.363
♪ Wherever is your heart
I call home ♪

42:12.363 --> 42:17.493
♪ Though your feet may take you
far from me, I know ♪

42:17.493 --> 42:22.915
♪ Wherever is your heart
I call home ♪

42:26.502 --> 42:54.906
♪
